arch:note.arch:string: The purpose of the daily journal was to record the activities taking place in a trench each day. This included which loci were excavated, how and why loci were excavated and the ongoing impressions of the relationships among loci. It should be noted that journals record the actions, impressions and ideas of trench supervisors during the excavations. They are not, therefore, the final interpretations or syntheses of the emerging data.

arch:internalDocument.arch:string:
August 16, 2001

Today is the last day of the dig so I will pull pottery out and we already started to cut the South baulk because it is possible that we will draw this one.

Also I will draw a last day plan. I will open a new locus for the pit that we saw yesterday. I am pulling out pottery from L4066 but these are suspicious because they are coming from the same area in the middle. This area shall be searched for a surface next year.

We took L4035 off, we knocked the walls down. The pottery around (oven) was thin.
